# Localize User-Facing Strings

- Do not add new inline user-facing English strings in Flutter UI, validators, dialogs, toasts, or error helpers.
- Add new copy to `lib/l10n/app_en.arb` and `lib/l10n/app_de.arb`, then regenerate `AppLocalizations`.
- Prefer `context.l10n` inside widgets and `currentAppLocalizations()` only in non-widget helpers that cannot access `BuildContext`.
- Reuse existing localization keys for common actions like retry, save, cancel, back, next, finish, and auth/profile/group labels before adding new ones.
- Keep backend fields, route names, IDs, and API payload keys unchanged; localize only user-facing display text.
